Warning‚ö†Ô∏è The Common ‚ÄúNew Line‚Äù Trap



There is a famous bug that confuses every beginner.
If you use nextInt() (to read a number) and immediately afterwards use nextLine() (to read text), the Scanner will skip the text input!
Why? When you type a number and hit Enter, nextInt() takes the number but leaves the ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù key press (newline character) in the memory. The next nextLine() reads that leftover ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù and thinks you finished typing.
The Fix: Add an extra nextLine() just to consume the leftover ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù.
int id = scanner.nextInt(); 

// Fix: Consume the leftover newline
scanner.nextLine(); 

String name = scanner.nextLine(); // Now this works!
